-{"id":"flywheel_connectors-1z643","title":"Hardening Sweep: eliminate hard-coded constants, placeholder implementations, and frozen API versions","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-25T03:04:45.686415Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-03-25T04:53:46.711916Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","hardening"],"comments":[{"id":1937,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-1z643","author":"jemanuel","text":"EPIC: Hardening Sweep (2026-03-25 audit by SunnyMoose)

A systematic code-level audit of the entire FCP workspace (28 core crates, 153 connectors, ~1.4M lines of Rust) uncovered several categories of issues that undermine production-readiness, correctness, and maintainability:

1. CRITICAL: Two connectors (DocuSign, Plaid) default to non-production environments (demo/sandbox URLs). Any deployment using defaults silently hits test infrastructure.

2. HIGH: Five connectors have placeholder implementations that look functional but are not: AWS SigV4 signing (affects AWS + S3), GCP JWT signing, DocuSign streaming, LLM-Router provider API calls. These pass tests but fail against real APIs.

3. HIGH: Four+ connectors freeze API version strings (Anthropic 2023-06-01, Notion 2022-06-28, Azure 2022-12-01, Salesforce v59.0) that are years out of date. Providers may deprecate or remove support for these versions.

4. MEDIUM: ~80+ connectors hard-code Duration::from_secs(30) for HTTP request timeouts with no environment-variable or manifest-based override. The infrastructure crates (fcp-streaming, fcp-webhook, fcp-sdk) also bake in timeout/buffer/retry constants that should be configurable per-connector or per-zone.

5. MEDIUM: Six connectors (firecrawl, huggingface, perplexity-search, tlon, zalo, zalouser) are scaffolded-only — they declare operations but return invoke_surface_unimplemented on all invocations. These need either implementation or honest demotion to 'stub' status.

6. LOW: Four TODO markers in fwc/src/bench_cmd.rs represent genuinely unfinished benchmark implementations (blocked on fcp-sdk, fcp-mesh, fcp-crypto Shamir). Template TODOs in fwc/src/new_cmd.rs are intentional and not actionable.

This epic organizes all findings into a dependency-aware task graph so they can be addressed systematically. The tree is structured so foundation work (configurable timeout infrastructure, API version management) unblocks the per-connector sweeps.","created_at":"2026-03-25T03:05:03Z"},{"id":1972,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-1z643","author":"BronzeStork","text":"Taking a narrow audit/fix slice under this hardening epic: the new fwc discovery/export validation path still panics on invalid operation/capability ids and silently drops invalid related capabilities even after the recent Result-based hardening. Reserved crates/fwc/src/readiness.rs and crates/fwc/src/export_tools.rs to convert the remaining panic/drop behavior into explicit validation errors with coverage.","created_at":"2026-03-25T04:08:19Z"},{"id":1973,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-1z643","author":"BronzeStork","text":"Audited recent fwc discovery/export hardening. Fixed incomplete panic/silent-drop handling for malformed discovery metadata by routing operation export through Result-returning validation, and corrected regressions/tests to target truly non-canonical IDs (uppercase/illegal-char cases, not merely non-fcp prefixes). Verification: rch exec -- cargo fmt --check -p fwc passed; rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/fwc-bronzestork cargo test -p fwc --no-run hit remote worker RCH-E307 (missing dbus-1.pc on worker), then local no-run build passed with the same target dir; exact rebuilt tests passed for readiness::try_operation_info_rejects_invalid_* and export_tools::try_export_tools_rejects_invalid_discovery_capability_ids.","created_at":"2026-03-25T04:31:02Z"}]}
